    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.9.0-dev\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, because they don't have this feature\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux Mint 20.3\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nterminator 1.91\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nOfficial dev PPA + apt\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n1. Open Neovim\r\n2. `:set cmdheight=0`\r\n3. Go to insert mode\r\n4. Go back to normal mode, **notice the lowest line disappearing**\r\n5. Go back to insert mode, **notice the \"-- INSERT --\" text appearing**\r\n6. To bring back the lowest line of the terminal, do something that redraws it, e.g. type a colon and press backspace\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNothing should happen to the lowest line of the terminal\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nLowest line of the terminal is either blank (in normal mode; you can still interact with characters) or contains a mode name (in insert mode), making it impossible to be read.",
